abstract: There had been signs of difficulty at the small company founded by the choreographer Jessica Lang.
snippet: There had been signs of difficulty at the small company founded by the choreographer Jessica Lang.
lead_paragraph: The end is near for Jessica Lang Dance: The small-but-vibrant company founded seven years ago by the choreographer Jessica Lang announced Monday that it would close this spring.

snippet: Once seen as crime scene detritus, bullets and ejected shell casings are now recognized as vital pieces of evidence.
lead_paragraph: PHILADELPHIA — In a series of brazen attacks a few summers back, a man known as the “ruthless robber” stole money from his victims and then opened fire on them, leaving little behind but wounded bodies and ejected shell casings.

abstract: The hedge fund billionaire Daniel Loeb’s latest activist push has him facing off against descendants of John T. Dorrance, who own more than 40 percent of Campbell and control three board seats.
snippet: The hedge fund billionaire Daniel Loeb’s latest activist push has him facing off against descendants of John T. Dorrance, who own more than 40 percent of Campbell and control three board seats.
lead_paragraph: Daniel Loeb is happy to play the barbarian at the gate. He’s got the money, about $3.1 billion. He’s got the office, a sleek white space that is a quintessential hedge fund aerie, with art by Jean-Michel Basquiat, Jeff Koons and Andy Warhol. And in taking on the old-money family that owns more than 40 percent of Campbell Soup Company, he’s found the perfect foil for his new-money ambitions.

abstract: City Center’s production of the landmark musical from 1975 is a pleasure, an education and a problem.
snippet: City Center’s production of the landmark musical from 1975 is a pleasure, an education and a problem.
lead_paragraph: When “A Chorus Line” opened on Broadway in 1975 — having step-ball-changed its way uptown from the New York Shakespeare Festival — it was the livingest thing in a dead zone. Over its 15-year run, its youthful vigor helped resuscitate the moribund theater district, and musical theater in general.

abstract: Old equipment in Palm Beach County prompted the elections supervisor to warn the county may not be able to meet the deadline in Florida’s statewide recount.
snippet: Old equipment in Palm Beach County prompted the elections supervisor to warn the county may not be able to meet the deadline in Florida’s statewide recount.
lead_paragraph: RIVIERA BEACH, Fla. — Jim Bonfiglio, a former mayor of a tiny coastal town south of Mar-a-Lago, lost his shot at a seat in the Florida Legislature in the midterm election last week by an agonizing 37 votes.

abstract: Crenshaw, a Texas Republican headed to Congress, used the moment to make an earnest plea for unity. But he also had a few jokes for Davidson up his sleeve.
snippet: Crenshaw, a Texas Republican headed to Congress, used the moment to make an earnest plea for unity. But he also had a few jokes for Davidson up his sleeve.
lead_paragraph: Pete Davidson apologized on “Saturday Night Live” this weekend to Dan Crenshaw, the former Navy SEAL and newly elected representative he mocked last week in a widely criticized “Weekend Update” segment. In a surprise cameo, Crenshaw appeared alongside Davidson to take a few humorous potshots of his own and then, more earnestly, to try to find some common ground.

abstract: He fired Jeff Sessions. But a House Democratic majority prepares to pounce.
snippet: He fired Jeff Sessions. But a House Democratic majority prepares to pounce.
lead_paragraph: Frank Bruni: Ross, I hope you got more sleep than I did on Tuesday night. If not, this could be a very interesting conversation. We need to discuss the midterms and, of course, Jeff Sessions, but first, because I’m reeling, that White House news conference! President Trump really does possess mystical powers, because after years of beholding him, I remain full of wonder. I am still taken aback: the pettiness, the meanness, the extravagant flights of pure fantasy. Oh, and the epic self-congratulation. “A hot White House,” he called it. Is the A.C. broken? He said that he yearns to be boring. Well, then I yearn to be a credenza. Have you grown numb to it?
